title: AlpacaHack Round 4 (Rev)
description: AlpacaHack is a new CTF platform for individual competitions. AlpacaHack Round 4 (Rev) is the 4th CTF hosted by the AlpacaHack team, featuring 4 Rev challenges. The challenges are designed with a wide range of difficulties, making them enjoyable for participants of all levels, including beginners. They are created by Xornet and keymoon.

title: IRON CTF 2024
description:
Welcome to the inaugural edition of IRON CTF (Intrusion Reconnaissance and Offensive Navigation CTF)!

Team 1nf1n1ty from SASTRA Deemed University invites you to embark on an exciting online Jeopardy-style Capture the Flag challenge. Whether you're just starting out or a seasoned hacker, this event promises the perfect platform to push your limits, hone your skills, and enjoy the thrill of competition.

Tackle diverse challenges in categories like Web Exploitation, Game Hacking, Reverse Engineering, Cryptography, Forensics, Binary Exploitation, and more.

Team Size: Maximum of 4 participants per team

Good luck, and happy hacking!

Stay updated by joining our Discord community: https://discord.com/invite/e6yRKphmuU

title: BRICS+ CTF Quals 2024
description:
We invite you to take a participation in cybersecurity international team competitions BRICS+ Capture The Flag. The qualification stage will be online in CTF Jeopardy format. The best teams will be able to compete in the final, which will be held online in CTF Attack-Defense format.

The CTF is for any academic/professional team from all around the world. Best teams from BRICS countries and international (all over the world) teams will be invited to the final round (Prize pool of the finals is 1 000 000 roubles). Before the final round we will ask eligible for the BRICS quota teams to verify their status.

More information about quals: https://brics-ctf.com/
prizes: Prize pool of the final round is 1 000 000 roubles
